当 MiniCPM VQA 同时接收到图像和视频信息时，它会仅处理视频信息而忽略图像信息。如果您想处理图像信息，请断开视频信息的输入。

When MiniCPM VQA simultaneously receives both image and video information, it processes only the video information while ignoring the image information. If you want to process the image information, please disconnect the input of the video information.

A quantum group is a mathematical structure that generalizes the concept of a classical group to include noncommutative elements. It is defined as a Hopf algebra over a field, which means it has both the structure of an algebra and a structure of a coalgebra, satisfying certain compatibility conditions.
In other words, a quantum group can be thought of as a set of operators or functions that satisfy certain algebraic properties, such as associativity and existence of inverses, but with additional features related to quantum mechanics, such as the possibility of measuring multiple quantities simultaneously or the uncertainty principle.
Quantum groups have applications in various areas of mathematics and physics, including representation theory, statistical mechanics, and quantum field theory. They are also used in computer science for cryptography and information security.
